==English==

===Noun===
'''freeway'''  (''plural:'' '''[[freeways]]''')
# ''American English'', ''International, Australian, Canadian, (New Zealand) English'': a [[highway]] with full [[access control]]; {{UK}} a [[dual carriageway]]. A freeway has no at-grade crossings of any kind. (The term refers to a road that is free-flowing, not to the absence of any charges.) 

===Individual classes===
These terms refer to classes of road - for instance not all freeways in the United Kingdom are motorways, but all motorways are freeways.
